
First Steps :

to make and test CSDS before any production , you need to create a virtual Lab with Virtual Box , VMware or proxmox ,... with 4 VM. 
VM's must be in the same LAN and Network adaptater must be set as Promiscuity mode Allow All

1. CSDS ( slackWare distro  )

Download latest Slackware distro from official repo :  https://mirrors.slackware.com/slackware/slackware-iso/
install as usual ext4 partitions and swap.( recommended size 100G for the Lab)
update & upgrade distro .  Important : after upgrade the kernel will be be updated . Bash LILO -V to update LILO . if not , LILO will not boot.
create a user and apply root privilège
create a directory : mkdir -p /opt/cybercity

2. Kali Linux or equivalent for penetration testing 
Download latest kali  distro from official repo : https://www.kali.org/get-kali
install as usual ext4 partitions and swap.( recommended size 40G for the Lab )

3 . Windows Server 2022 or 2025 evaluation release ( no activation key needed for the lab)
Download latest from official repo : https://www.microsoft.com//evalcenter
install as usual NTFS partition ( recommended size 40G for the Lab )
install services ( AD , LDAP , DNS , IIS , RDP , ... )

4.Ubuntu Server
Download latest ubuntu distro from official repo : https://ubuntu.com/download/server
install as usual ext4 partitions and swap.( recommended size 40G for the Lab )
update & upgrade distro then install services
